method.name: DecodeTLV(System.Byte[], System.Int32&, out System.Byte&, out System.Int32&, out System.Byte[]&)

property.name: Message
property.value: Use of this API is highly discouraged, it selects legacy-mode LM/NTLM authentication, which sends your password in very weak encryption over the wire even if the server supports the more secure NTLMv2 / NTLMv2 Session. You need to use the new `Type3Message (Type2Message)' constructor to use the more secure NTLMv2 / NTLMv2 Session authentication modes. These require the Type 2 message from the server to compute the response.
